{"title_page": "Linda Olsson (actress)", "text_new": "[[File:Linda Olsson 2019.jpg|thumb|200px|Linda Olsson as Jane Smart in the musical Witches of Eastwick at Cirkus in 2019 ]]\n\n'''Linda Olsson''', (born 8 August 1979 in [[Lind\u00f6]]) is a Swedish musical artist, dancer and actress.\n\nLinda Olsson grew up in a doctors family in Lind\u00f6 and studied at L\u00e5ngtorpsskolan and later at Navestadsskolans music classes and later she studied music at De Geergymnasiet. She has also studied dance at Lagers dansinstitut in [[Norrk\u00f6ping]]. She has won gold in latinamerican dance and Swedish championship silver in bug dancing. She has also studied ballet at Balettakademin  in [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/morgondagens-lovande-stjarnor/|title=Morgondagens lovande stj\u00e4rnor|website=Expressen|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n \nShe got her big breakthrough as the lead role in the musical [[Mary Poppins (musical)|Mary Poppins]] in 2008 at [[G\u00f6teborgsoperan]].<ref name=\"auto\">[https://www.skd.se/2017/02/07/hon-graver-pa-djupet-i-dubbel-musikalkaraktar/ Hon gr\u00e4ver p\u00e5 djupet i dubbel musikalkarakt\u00e4r] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170530010125/http://www.skd.se/2017/02/07/hon-graver-pa-djupet-i-dubbel-musikalkaraktar/ |date=2017-05-30}} skd.se Retrieved 27 March 2020</ref> She has also acted in [[Grease (musical)|Grease]], [[A Chorus Line]] and [[Kiss Me, Kate (musical)|Kiss Me Kate]]. She acted in Rivierans guldgossar at [[Cirkus]] in [[Stockholm]] in 2007. And in The Producers - Det v\u00e5ras f\u00f6r Hitler in 2010 at Galateatern. She has as well appeared in musicals [[Sweeney Todd (musical)|Sweeney Todd]] and [[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> She also had a role in the very first [[ABBA]] music fest ''Mamma Mia! The Party'' at [[Tyrol]] in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/nyheter/silvia-showade-med-mamma-mia-artisterna/|title=H\u00e4r showar Silvia med Mamma Mia-artisterna|website=Expressen|accessdate=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807110406/http://www.expressen.se/nyheter/silvia-showade-med-mamma-mia-artisterna/|archive-date=7 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Olsson played the lead role as Dale Tremont in [[Top Hat (musical)|Top Hat]] at [[Malm\u00f6 Opera]] in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.malmoopera.se/medverkande/linda-olsson|title=Linda Olsson|date=13 October 2015|website=Malm\u00f6 Opera|accessdate=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526161153/https://www.malmoopera.se/medverkande/linda-olsson|archive-date=26 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nSince 2017, she is married to singer [[Tommy Nilsson]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hant.se/noje/tommy-nilssons-nya-brollopsbesked-med-19-ar-yngre-linda/|title=Tommy Nilssons nya br\u00f6llopsbesked med 19 \u00e5r yngre Linda|date=10 May 2017|website=H\u00e4nt.se|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Olsson, Linda}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Swedish actors]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Linda Olsson 2019.jpg|thumb|200px|Linda Olsson as Jane Smart in the musical Witches of Eastwick at Cirkus in 2019 ]]\n\n'''Linda Olsson''', (born 8 August 1979 in [[Lind\u00f6]]) is a Swedish musical artist, dancer and actress.\n\nLinda Olsson grew up in a doctors family in Lind\u00f6 and studied at L\u00e5ngtorpsskolan and later at Navestadsskolans music classes and later she studied music at De Geergymnasiet. She has also studied dance at Lagers dansinstitut in [[Norrk\u00f6ping]]. She has won gold in latinamerican dance and Swedish championship silver in bug dancing. She has also studied ballet at Balettakademin  in [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/morgondagens-lovande-stjarnor/|title=Morgondagens lovande stj\u00e4rnor|website=Expressen|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n \nShe got her big breakthrough as the lead role in the musical [[Mary Poppins (musical)|Mary Poppins]] in 2008 at [[G\u00f6teborgsoperan]].<ref name=\"auto\">[https://www.skd.se/2017/02/07/hon-graver-pa-djupet-i-dubbel-musikalkaraktar/ Hon gr\u00e4ver p\u00e5 djupet i dubbel musikalkarakt\u00e4r] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170530010125/http://www.skd.se/2017/02/07/hon-graver-pa-djupet-i-dubbel-musikalkaraktar/ |date=2017-05-30}} skd.se Retrieved 27 March 2020</ref> She has also acted in [[Grease]], [[A Chorus Line]] and [[Kiss Me, Kate (musical)|Kiss Me Kate]]. She acted in Rivierans guldgossar at [[Cirkus]] in [[Stockholm]] in 2007. And in The Producers - Det v\u00e5ras f\u00f6r Hitler in 2010 at Galateatern. She has as well appeared in musicals [[Sweeney Todd (musical)|Sweeney Todd]] and [[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]].<ref name=\"auto\"/> She also had a role in the very first [[ABBA]] music fest ''Mamma Mia! The Party'' at [[Tyrol]] in 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/nyheter/silvia-showade-med-mamma-mia-artisterna/|title=H\u00e4r showar Silvia med Mamma Mia-artisterna|website=Expressen|accessdate=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807110406/http://www.expressen.se/nyheter/silvia-showade-med-mamma-mia-artisterna/|archive-date=7 August 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Olsson played the lead role as Dale Tremont in [[Top Hat (musical)|Top Hat]] at [[Malm\u00f6 Opera]] in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.malmoopera.se/medverkande/linda-olsson|title=Linda Olsson|date=13 October 2015|website=Malm\u00f6 Opera|accessdate=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190526161153/https://www.malmoopera.se/medverkande/linda-olsson|archive-date=26 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nSince 2017, she is married to singer [[Tommy Nilsson]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hant.se/noje/tommy-nilssons-nya-brollopsbesked-med-19-ar-yngre-linda/|title=Tommy Nilssons nya br\u00f6llopsbesked med 19 \u00e5r yngre Linda|date=10 May 2017|website=H\u00e4nt.se|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Olsson, Linda}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n[[Category:Swedish actors]]\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toGrease(link changed toGrease (musical)) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linda_Olsson_(actress)"}
